text: Stained with a lipstick shade you don’t use.
When was the last time she was here?
When will she be here again?
If I called her, would she come?
A gift from our first date…
Now she bursts through the door expecting me to not say anything.
A song and dace we both know by memory now…
Pio I know you didn’t wanted to come here but dude.
I hate to be the one telling you this but dude.
I’m looking at, like, RIGHT in front of me. I’m looking at Prava making out with another girl.
I told you they were evil. Girlie I told you this woman was bad for you.
I TOLD YOU… Wait, I’m going to make a fucking mess and I’ll be right back.
With holes for wings you don’t have.
It goes through you when she has nothing better to do.
The smell is stuck in it…
Is that how you call me?
Your little mistakes that we all make.
Tell her that I love her, that I adore her.
That she makes my head dizzy, and without her I have nothing.
That she’s extraordinary with her tongue?
I don’t even recognize myself anymore…
I had enough of this useless circus.
A deal between me and myself
Rot away in self-deprecation and sorrow…
makes me sicker that any lingering traces of old fucks ever could.
Is a price to be paid in jealousy and eternal highways.
